# PR Description Generator

Whenever a new pull request is opened, write a new pull request description based on the changes/diff made in the PR. This will run when a PR is opened and when new commits are pushed to that PR. If you've already added a summary to the body but another commit was pushed, make sure to update the summary again based on any new changes that were made.

## Guidelines

- Be short, concise, and to the point
- Format the description in valid markdown
- Use code blocks to show the diff or example code when the change is small or when it makes sense
- Provide a high-level summary rather than listing every file changed
- Include the motivation for the change if it can be inferred
- Note any breaking changes or migration steps needed